
---


@startuml

' Define classes
class Location {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +description: String
  -exhibitions: List<Exhibition>
}

class Exhibition {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date
  +coordinator: Employee
  -exhibitionItems: List<ExhibitionItem>
}

class ExhibitionItem {
  +id: String
  +itemName: String
  +description: String
  -piecesRequested: List<Piece>
}

class Piece {
  +id: String
  +title: String
  +artist: String
  +year: Integer
  +collector: Collector
}

class Collector {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +contactInfo: String
  -pieces: List<Piece>
}

class Employee {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +position: String
  -coach: Employee
  -coachedEmployees: List<Employee>
}

' Relationships
Location "1" -- "0..*" Exhibition : has
Exhibition "1" -- "1..*" ExhibitionItem : contains
ExhibitionItem "1" -- "0..*" Piece : requests
Piece "1" -- "1" Collector : belongs to
Employee "1" -- "0..1" Employee : coach
Employee "1" -- "0..*" Employee : coached by

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Relationships:

- **Location ↔ Exhibition**: A location can host multiple exhibitions.
- **Exhibition ↔ ExhibitionItem**: An exhibition consists of multiple exhibition items.
- **ExhibitionItem ↔ Piece**: Each item may request one or more pieces from collectors.
- **Piece ↔ Collector**: A piece is sourced from a collector.
- **Employee ↔ Coach**: Employees can be coaches or have coaches (a hierarchical relationship).
- **Employee ↔ Coached Employees**: A senior employee can coach multiple junior employees.

